   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "[Guix 1.4.0 has been out for nearly 1 year.](https://guix.gnu.org/en/blog/2022/gnu-guix-1.4.0-released/) Our current docs ([contrib/guix/INSTALL.md](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/contrib/guix/INSTALL.md)) mostly describe installing 1.3.0, and it's related dependencies. Updating the guide for 1.4.0 could simplify many things. i.e rather than discussing Guile 3.0 vs 2.0, and installation instructions/build complication for either version, we [can settle on just 3.0](https://guix.gnu.org/manual/en/html_node/Requirements.html). I have done a from-source build of Guix, on Ubuntu Jammy, using distro packaged deps, and everything seems to be working as expected.",
